review_blob: 33cl bottle. rgng 2010. 15C. Pours brownred with small, disappearing head. Aroma: creamy, buttery, bit spicy. Light body, toast, slightly salty. Distinct pomegranate after taste, dry. Better than expected. Pleasant beer.

33cl bottle. Drinking temperature:15C. Pours brownred with good head. Aroma full of prunes. Thin body for 11% ABV. Sweetish, sparkling, light chocolate. Alcohol well hidden. I love the label that delivers what it promises: an obscure, dark beer,strong in taste, heavy on alcohol. Good beer!

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Bottle (bottlingdate: 10/09/2010). Drank it at 10 degrees Celsius. Pours cloudy beige/brown which always makes me thirsty. Head disappears soon after pouring but lasts as a very thin layer. Tastes sweet, vinous, thick, complex. Lots of licorice. Lots of dark fruits, like in Christmas pudding. Some vanilla. Some roastiness. Warming mouthfeel (12% ABV). Sweet/roastiness lingering long. Beer is Art!
